org.opentcs.util.eventsystem

Class EventHub<E extends Event>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.opentcs.util.eventsystem.EventHub<E>
  • Type Parameters:
    E - The actual event implementation.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    EventListener<E>, EventSource<E>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AsynchronousEventHub, SynchronousEventHub
    Deprecated. 
    For event handling, use classes in org.opentcs.util.event instead.

    @Deprecated
 @ScheduledApiChange(when="5.0",
                    details="Will be removed.")
public abstract class EventHub<E extends Event>
extends java.lang.Object
implements EventListener<E>, EventSource<E>
    An EventHub dispatches events to registered listeners. A client, i.e. an EventListener, may register with an EventHub for receiving events. The EventHub will forward any events received to the client either synchronously (i.e. in the context of the thread calling processEvent()) or asynchronously (i.e. in a separate thread).
